The Hawks have on Wednesday swopped in to seize assets worth a whopping R46 million allegedly defrauded from a Midrand based medical equipment company’s coffers by a former employee. The afternoon raid took place in Boksburg, East of Johannesburg. The 43-year-old old woman worked as an accountant at the company and allegedly defrauded the company by depositing money into her deceased husband’s account. According to on the ground reports, the woman was summoned from the Sun City luxury resort by the Hawks who informed her that they have a warrant for her arrest and to search her property. During the seizure, up to nine luxury cars were taken. While seven safes containing cash and jewelry totaling millions were emptied. According to reports, the Boksburg home is only one of a number of properties that are still to be searched. -TNA Reporter